headline.main: BRITISH SEA LOSSES SET LOW FOR SPRING; 17 Ships Totaling 59,141 Tons in Week Ended March 23 Listed by Admiralty NAZIS CLAIM 5 TANKERS Credit Bombers With Sinking Craft Off Ireland -- 2 More Added to One Day's Toll

lead_paragraph: LONDON, April 1 -- The figures for merchant shipping losses for the week ended March 23, show, for one reason or another -- admittedly not known definitely to the British -- the lowest total for several weeks.
